.TH TOTPGATE 1 2026-05-28 "totpgate" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
totpgate \- send a TOTP authorization packet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B totpgate
\fB\-\-secret\fR \fIsecret\fR [\fIoptions\fR] \fIserver\fR [\fItarget_port\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtotpgate\fR generates a TOTP token from the shared secret and sends it
as a UDP datagram to the daemon running on \fIserver\fR. Optionally
overrides the target TCP port in the authorization request.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-secret\fR \fIsecret\fR
Shared secret. Base32 by default; prefix with \fBhex:\fR or \fBb64:\fR
for other encodings. (required)
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fIport\fR
UDP port of the target daemon. (default: 2222)
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Display usage and exit.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIserver\fR
IP address or hostname of the \fBtotpgated\fR daemon. (required)
.TP
\fItarget_port\fR
Optional TCP port override sent in the auth packet. If omitted the
daemon uses its configured \fB\-\-target-port\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.P
\fBtotpgate\fR exits 0 on success, 1 on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR totpgated (1)
